Definition: the doctrine that kings derive their right to rule directly from God and are not accountable to their subjects
Example: rebellion is the worst of political crimes; the doctrine of the divine right of kings was enunciated by the Stuarts in Britain in the 16th century
Synonyms: divine_right_of_kings, doctrine, the, that, kings, derive, their, right, to, rule, directly, from, God, and, are, not, accountable, subjects, rebellion, is, worst, of, political, crimes, divine, was, enunciated, by, Stuarts, in, Britain, th, century
Category: noun.cognition
